<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-22-0897 </DOCNO><TEXT>The motion is that the Food Protection (Emergency Prohibitions) (No. 3)Order 1987 be approved. This controls the movement and slaughter of sheepfrom certain areas of Cumbria, North Wales and Scotland following thereactor accident at Chernobyl in April 1986. The events leading to theintroduction of restrictions are outlined and the current situation explained.635 holdings and 746,000 sheep are under restrictions (November 1987)although earlier in 1987 these numbers had been lower. Apart from theParliamentary Under-Secretary who introduced the motion, one other speakeris reported verbatim and his speech generally approved the steps thegovernment had taken to control high radioactivity entering the foodchain. It is confirmed that research on the predicting the behaviourof radiocesium in the environment is being sponsored by the government.The debate lasted about half an hour. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>